headline.print_headline: Ukraine Prompts Fresh U.S. Look at Use of Russian Rocket Engines
headline.main: Ukraine Prompts Fresh U.S. Look at Use of Russian Rocket Engines

lead_paragraph: The Pentagon is going to take a fresh look at U.S. reliance on Russian-built engines to power American rockets that launch large U.S. government satellites into orbit, in light of the Ukraine crisis, Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel told Congress on Thursday.
